<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 6:56PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Widespread moderate to heavy snow will persist this evening.
* Snowfall rates between a half-inch to an inch will be likely
through 9 PM. 1 to 2 inches of new accumulation will be
possible during this time.
* East-northeast winds around 15 to 20 mph with gusts to 30 mph.
Highly fluctuating visibilities down to a quarter-mile are
possible given the breezy conditions and snow rates.
* Temperatures range between 32 to 33 degrees F.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow will lead to slippery roads, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Moderate to heavy snow will bring a reduction in visibility
down to a quarter-mile at times.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
